The paper deals with the problem of optimising control policies for a robot to complete a race track in minimum time, using Bayesian optimisation. This involves learning from an initial example, monitoring the robot's position, and searching efficiently over high-dimensional policy-parameter spaces. The paper thus covers topics related to machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), control systems (cs.SY), and computer vision (cs.CV).
